Operations

Purpose:
- Public-safe current operations memory for verification, deployment, packaging, live-site gates, and blocked external dependencies.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with deployment and readiness reports before relying on it.
Memory scope: current operational gates, deploy boundaries, and safe runbook pointers.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this local file when operational gates change; submit durable public-safe operations summaries to https://memoryendpoints.com/api/matm/memory-events/submit when authenticated.
Source of truth: `docs/deployment.md`, `docs/verification.md`, `docs/reports/final-readiness-report.md`, deploy attempt reports, and live verifier reports.
Next action for agents: keep local evidence separate from live evidence and never claim completion while deploy, live dogfood, or CI gates remain blocked.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, FTP host/user/password values, private handoff payloads, or raw one-time keys.

Current operations state:
- Local WSGI verification is the current reliable code-path proof.
- Package generation excludes `.git`, `.github`, `.uai`, root `workspace.uai`, root `reports/`, local prompts, raw handoff buckets, runtime stores, databases, logs, caches, credential handoff files, and deployment packages.
- Latest-code MemoryEndpoints.com live deployment remains gated by FTPS login failure before upload.
- MultiAgentMemory.com static source is present locally, but live publish remains gated by FTPS login failure before upload.
- GitHub Actions currently does not prove code health because the job fails before execution due to account or billing lock state.
- Live public route verification proves the currently deployed public surface only. It does not prove that the newest local code is deployed.
- Live authenticated dogfood must be rerun after the latest route/storage tranche is deployed.
